Module mesakit.map.geography
Package com.telenav.mesakit.map.geography.indexing.rtree

Class RTreeSpatialIndex<Element extends Bounded & Intersectable>

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.mesakit.map.geography.indexing.rtree.RTreeSpatialIndex<Element>
Type Parameters:
Element - An element must be Bounded, and Intersectable in order to be spatially indexed by an r-tree.
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.NamedObject, Bounded
Direct Known Subclasses:
BorderSpatialIndex, SegmentRTreeSpatialIndex
public class RTreeSpatialIndex<Element extends Bounded & Intersectable> extends Object implements Bounded, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.NamedObject
An r-tree spatial index with a simple linear splitting algorithm that sorts elements by latitude and longitude of their center and picks the two most distant as the beginning of the split. Otherwise, this is a linear r-tree as described in http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/R-tree.
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
